      <hedline>
        <hl1>Cut Car Emissions</hl1>
        <hl2 class="online_headline">Cut Car Emissions</hl2>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bluewater Network official Russell Long letter on July 8 editorial notes group drafted California law to cut greenhouse gas emissions from passenger vehicles because of Pres Bush's head-in-the-sand approach to global warming</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''California Leads on Warming'' (editorial, July 8):</p>
        <p>Our organization drafted the California legislation to reduce greenhouse gas emissions from passenger vehicles precisely because of President Bush's head-in-the-sand approach to this issue.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="online_lead_paragraph">
        <p>Cut Car Emissions To the Editor:.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''California Leads on Warming'' (editorial, July 8):</p>
        <p>Our organization drafted the California legislation to reduce greenhouse gas emissions from passenger vehicles precisely because of President Bush's head-in-the-sand approach to this issue.</p>
        <p>His call for adaptation to climate change is appalling. How does one adapt to devastated coastlines, increased wildfires, more droughts and an influx of dangerous tropical diseases?</p>
        <p>We believe that the California bill will help reduce global warming by forcing the use of cleaner vehicle technologies that have been sitting on the shelves, thereby giving motorists superior choices that will save money and reduce foreign oil dependence. Mr. Bush would be well advised to ask Congress to pass similar legislation.</p>
        <p>RUSSELL LONG  Exec. Dir., Bluewater Network  San Francisco, July 8, 2002</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
